3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with the development of a benchmark for visual recognition tasks, which is a common area of research in AI. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the organisation of the dataset in a three-level hierarchy, which could be relevant to information retrieval tasks. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with a dataset of images and presents baseline results for visual recognition tasks, which are common in multimedia research.
